 Medical background Pancreatic cancer is the fourth leading cause of cancer-related death in the United States.

 This disease is associated with a high mortality rate: the 5-year survival rate is estimated to be 4%.

 This is mainly due to the fact that the disease is often discovered at an already advanced disease state, which carries a dismal prognosis.

